The paper deals with the problem of data clustering with high space constraints, which is a common issue in many real-world applications. The method presented in the paper is based on graph sketching and density-based clustering, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DM), information retrieval (cs.IR), and databases (cs.DB). However, since the paper focuses on the algorithmic and theoretical aspects of the method, rather than on specific applications, we consider cs.DS and cs.LG as the most likely categories, followed by cs.DM, cs.SI, and cs.DB.
